cs.PF, cs.DC, cs.AR, cs.OS, cs.SE 

The paper discusses a methodology for optimizing multithreaded system scalability on multi-core platforms, which is relevant to several sub-categories. The most likely category is cs.PF (Performance), as the paper focuses on measuring and improving the performance of applications on multi-core systems. The second likely category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), as the paper deals with parallelism and scalability on multi-core platforms. The third likely category is cs.AR (Architecture), as the paper discusses the design space of multi-core systems. The fourth likely category is cs.OS (Operating Systems), as the paper touches on the interaction between applications and the operating system on multi-core platforms. The fifth likely category is cs.SE (Software Engineering), as the paper proposes a methodology for optimizing application scalability.
